# UI Style and Theming Rule

CSS must produce a clean, professional visual design as the default experience.

## Style quality requirements

- Maintain consistent spacing, typography, and visual hierarchy.
- Keep component styles coherent and avoid ad-hoc one-off visual behavior.
- Preserve readability, contrast, and interaction clarity for common states (default/hover/active/disabled/focus).

## User style adaptation requirements

- Build styles so user adaptation can be added cleanly (theme tokens, CSS custom properties, or equivalent).
- Keep style decisions configurable through explicit theme variables, not scattered hard-coded values.
- Define clear extension points for future user-selected themes/modes without breaking defaults.

## Delivery checklist (substantial UI/CSS changes)

- Confirm the default look remains clean and professional.
- Confirm new styles are compatible with planned user adaptation points.
- Update public style/theming documentation when style APIs or tokens change.

## Icon catalog

All toolbar icons live in `frontend/public/icons/toolbar/`. They share a common
SVG style: `viewBox="0 0 24 24"`, `fill="none"`, `stroke="#1f2937"`,
`stroke-width="2"` (or 1.75 for icons with filled sub-elements), `stroke-linecap="round"`,
`stroke-linejoin="round"`. Inline SVGs (e.g. in game tabs) use `fill="currentColor"`.

**Before adding a new icon, check this catalog.** If a purpose is already mapped,
reuse the existing file — do not create a second icon for the same semantic action.

| File | Purpose / semantic meaning |
|---|---|
| `nav-first.svg` | Navigate to first move |
| `nav-prev.svg` | Navigate to previous move |
| `nav-next.svg` | Navigate to next move |
| `nav-last.svg` | Navigate to last move |
| `save.svg` | **Save** — floppy disk shape; used in TextEditorSidebar and (inline variant) in game tab pills. Do NOT use an arrow-down for save — that means download. |
| `download.svg` | **Download** — arrow pointing down to a horizontal line; use only for export/download actions, never for save. |
| `undo.svg` | Undo last edit |
| `redo.svg` | Redo last undone edit |
| `default-indent.svg` | Apply default variation indentation |
| `indent.svg` | Increase indentation |
| `linebreak.svg` | Insert line break (`[[br]]` marker) |
| `comment-left.svg` | Insert comment before move |
| `comment-right.svg` | Insert comment after move |
| `metadata-columns.svg` | Toggle metadata column view |
| `mode-plain.svg` | PGN layout mode: Plain (raw/code — `< >` brackets) |
| `mode-text.svg` | PGN layout mode: Text (narrative prose — paragraph lines) |
| `mode-tree.svg` | PGN layout mode: Tree (variation tree — trunk + branches) |
| `game-id.svg` | **Game ID** — hash glyph; resource table id column + sort header (not for “new ID” features) |
